50|$|The F1 was {{introduced}} during World War II and subsequently redesigned post-war. It has a steel exterior that is notched to facilitate fragmentation upon detonation {{and to prevent}} hands from slipping. The distance the grenade can be thrown is estimated at 30-45 meters. The radius of the <b>shrapnel</b> <b>dispersion</b> is up to 200 meters (effective radius is about 30 meters, by some sources (Russian)). Hence, the grenade has to be deployed from a defensive position to avoid harm.|$|E

